				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Iksar Hide Mask...<a name="58868"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 24 04 11:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Grats on your mask. 
<br />

<br />
I thought I'd post some info here about the camp for those that don't have the mask yet. Years ago when I used to play a druid, I used to live on the forager cycle. Here's the lowdown. 
<br />

<br />
If your comming out of the cave that leads to the swamp of no hope, go right and keep the zone wall on your right. On your left you'll see a small stream. Keep following the zone wall untill you see the stream go out into the middle of the zone, between 2 hills. Stop, that's your safe spot and the best place to track the foragers. Allways bring the forager 
<br />
back to that spot to kill so as to minimize getting adds. 
<br />

<br />
And now for the fight. After you kill it, check your tracking, there will either be a named on track or a forager. If you kill a named and then check tracking chances are you won't see anything on track and assume that the cycle is broken. What actually happens is that after you kill a named, it spawns the forager on the other side of the zone out of your tracking range. When this happens, keep the zone wall on your left and follow it around as if your heading to sebelis. Go past the 
<br />
emerald jungle zone untill you get to a large wall with a pass through. On the otherside of the wall is a broken down iksar city with iksar ghosts floating around, (sebelis is also located in that city). Stop at that pass through and hit tracking and you should see the forager. Kill it and run back, the cycle will resume. 
<br />

<br />
Pulling Droknik. I've heard some people have a hard time pulling this guy. I play a low level bard so I'm a little hesitant to comment. If it were me I would charm him and pull him to the safe spot, then melee him and chain cast mez so he can't cast on you. Just a thought. 
<br />

<br />
I hope this helps. 
<br />
</span></td>
