				<td colspan="2"><span>Ledfoot got it right.  However, if you keep heading down the zone wall past the river you will come to a nice wide open spot to chant kite in.  Also, the guy with the iksar breast plate always spawns in that area, just over the hill, so you will be close to him if he pops and really he is the only mob that you have to worry about someone getting to before you.  Dronik spawns farther to the north from that area but is still within tracking range.
<br />

<br />
Also everyone that said the forgar will sometimes spawn near seb is correct.  If you do not have one on track near the swamp entrance then head north and then east across the zone.  If you do not pick it up on track head around south once past the lake and you will eventually find him.</span></td>
